wikipedia_page.main: Edward Baker (c. 1775 – 24 February 1862) was an English politician in the Conservative Party. He was the Member of Parliament (MP) for Wilton in Wiltshire from 1823 to 1830. He was re-elected unopposed at the 1837 general election, but stood down from the House of Commons at the 1841 general election.
